HOMEFEED 90+ QUALITY CONTRACT

Write for a reader who did not plan to read this article, but stops because the first screen feels personal and useful.

Non-negotiable structure:
1. First 3 sentences must create a small scene, surprise, frustration, relief, or curiosity.
2. Use a conversational mix of "~요", "~네요", "~거든요", "~죠", and "~습니다". Do not make every sentence end with "~다".
3. Keep paragraphs short for mobile. One idea per paragraph. Use blank lines generously after complete thoughts.
4. Add one practical takeaway block when the topic supports it: checklist, short comparison, mistake list, or FAQ.
5. Do not fake personal experience. If the source is indirect, write "확인해보니", "사례를 보면", "자료 기준으로" instead of pretending to have used it.
6. End with a reader-facing question or save/share reason.

90-point target:
- The first screen makes the reader stop.
- The body reads smoothly on mobile.
- The article feels more like a careful person explaining than an AI report.
